  "prompt": "Are there any websites like DAAD for masters in US?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several organizations and websites similar to DAAD that provide comprehensive information, resources, and scholarship opportunities for international students aspiring to pursue a master's degree in the United States. Here are some notable ones:\n\n1. **EducationUSA**\n   - **Website:** [educationUSA.state.gov](https://educationusa.state.gov/)\n   - **Description:** A U.S. Department of State network of over 430 international advising centers in more than 175 countries. EducationUSA offers accurate, comprehensive, and current information about studying in the U.S., including guidance on applications, scholarships, and visa processes.\n\n2. **Fulbright Program**\n   - **Website:** [foreign.fulbrightonline.org](https://foreign.fulbrightonline.org/)\n   - **Description:** Managed by the U.S. government, the Fulbright Program offers prestigious scholarships for international students to study, conduct research, or teach in the United States. It emphasizes cultural exchange and academic excellence.\n\n3. **Institute of International Education (IIE)**\n   - **Website:** [iie.org](https://www.iie.org/)\n   - **Description:** IIE manages numerous scholarship programs, including the Fulbright and the Gilman scholarships. Their website provides information on various funding opportunities and resources for studying in the U.S.\n\n4. **Scholarships.com**\n   - **Website:** [scholarships.com](https://www.scholarships.com/)\n   - **Description:** A comprehensive database of scholarships and grants for international students. Users can search for funding opportunities based on their country of origin, field of study, and other criteria.\n\n5. **Peterson\u2019s**\n   - **Website:** [petersons.com](https://www.petersons.com/)\n   - **Description:** Offers a wide range of resources for students seeking higher education in the U.S., including information on colleges, graduate programs, standardized tests, and scholarship opportunities.\n\n6. **CampusUSA (Managed by IIE)**\n   - **Website:** [campususa.org](https://www.campususa.org/)\n   - **Description:** Provides resources and tools for international students to explore U.S. higher education options, connect with institutions, and find scholarship information.\n\n7. **U.S. Department of State - Scholarships and Fellowships**\n   - **Website:** [state.gov/e/peace/scholarships](https://www.state.gov/e/peace/scholarships/)\n   - **Description:** Offers information on various scholarship programs sponsored by the U.S. government, including those focused on promoting mutual understanding and peace.\n\n8. **Fastweb**\n   - **Website:** [fastweb.com](https://www.fastweb.com/)\n   - **Description:** One of the largest free scholarship search engines. Students can create a profile to receive personalized scholarship matches based on their background and academic interests.\n\n9. **International Scholarships**\n   - **Website:** [internationalscholarships.com](https://www.internationalscholarships.com/)\n   - **Description:** A platform dedicated to helping international students find scholarships to study abroad, including in the United States. It provides detailed listings and application guidance.\n\n10. **Common App**\n    - **Website:** [commonapp.org](https://www.commonapp.org/)\n    - **Description:** While primarily known for undergraduate admissions, the Common App also provides resources and links to scholarships and financial aid options for graduate studies.\n\n**Additional Tips:**\n\n- **University Websites:** Many U.S. universities offer their own scholarships and assistantships for international graduate students. It\u2019s beneficial to visit the official websites of the institutions you\u2019re interested in to explore specific funding opportunities.\n\n- **Local Organizations and Foundations:** Sometimes, local governments, non-profits, and private organizations in your home country offer scholarships or grants for studying abroad. Researching these can provide additional funding avenues.\n\n- **Professional Associations:** Depending on your field of study, professional bodies related to your discipline may offer scholarships or grants for advanced studies.\n\nBefore applying, ensure you carefully review the eligibility criteria, application deadlines, and required documents for each scholarship or program. It's also advisable to start the application process well in advance to meet all necessary deadlines.",
